##Chinese New Year's Eve after 95 young man squatted in the factory for three days, for Hubei Relatives and friends sent out tens of thousands of masks | deep net

Micro-signal Qqshenwang

Features, tencent news products, deep web is an original in-depth report that digs into the hidden stories of popular companies, events and people in the technology and TMT fields to explore the deep logic behind them.

By Ma Guanxia
Produced by Xiaoman Studio

Welcome to download tencent news APP for more quality information

This Spring Festival, Hubei Wuhan and other places have been affected by the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic, in the face of a serious situation of prevention and control, the community have taken action and rushed to Wuhan. While enterprises and stars donate money and materials, some ordinary people are also doing their best to support Hubei Wuhan.

Dai Yuan, a 1995-year-old man who could not return to his hometown of Huanggang for Chinese New Year and lives in Anqing, Anhui Province, found some mask factories around the city after learning that relatives and friends in Wuhan, Huanggang and other places could not buy masks and other supplies, from twenty-nine, New Year's Eve to the first day of the three days have been for epidemic areas of friends to collect tens of thousands of pairs of masks.

Dai described two of the difficulties he had faced over the past three days in trying to raise money for masks in the affected areas. On the one hand, supplies of masks were scarce, factories were not entirely in production during the Spring Festival, and many factories were already facing shortages of raw materials On the other hand, after the closure of Wuhan, many express routes into the city have been blocked, logistics is not as smooth as usual, some SF express pressure in Wuhan, has not yet reached the hands of friends.

"No matter how far the factory is, I run. "

I came from Hubei Province and later settled in Anqing because of my parents'work. In the past few years, my family usually spent the Lunar New Year's Eve in Anqing. On the first day of the Lunar New Year, we went back to visit relatives in our hometown in Hubei Province.

Wuhan outbreak, this year can not go home to Hubei, see all the changes in their own can not help, especially anxious psychology. I saw in the news news that medical supplies in the affected areas were particularly scarce, and I wanted to do my bit, so I found some factories around Anhui to deliver supplies to relatives, friends and medical institutions in my hometown.

I initially searched the Internet and on a map of Josiah Goddard, and when I saw a mask manufacturer with contact information, I called, but many of the calls went unanswered during Chinese New Year. After collecting some manufacturers I figured out the contact information and address, and then drove in Anhui side of the search.

It took me about an hour and a half to find a factory that was still working, but everyone was busy, everyone was working, trucks and cars were loading outside.

I asked the factory whether there is any goods, the other side thought that I want to buy, tell me no goods, now on the table goods and goods in processing have been ordered.

I couldn't get the goods at that time very anxious, went to negotiate with the boss, tell him I was for Hubei's relatives and friends to buy, we come all the way over here must get some goods for us. Then the boss gave me about 3,000 masks, these masks are really not easy to come.

I thought all the delivery companies were out of service, but a search revealed that SF express and post were still available. I found the nearest SF outlet and sent it to relatives and friends in Wuhan on the night of January 23, twenty-nine. They told me that masks were in short supply in the hospitals and pharmacies there. More and more people in Wuhan, Hubei, contacted me through them. At that time I was thinking, no matter what factory, no matter how far, I will go to run, to find the source.

The masks were transported to Wuhan through the Red Cross

Later, I encountered new problems, in addition to the supply of masks is particularly scarce, into Hubei Province logistics transport channel has also changed, Wuhan closed, many access to the city have been blocked. I searched the Internet for ways to transport goods into Hubei, and also asked some relatives in Hubei. I learned that there are two ways to transport goods into Wuhan, one of which is through the Red Cross.

I have two friends in Beijing also want to donate a batch of masks to Wuhan, they asked logistics, logistics reply is already unable to send to Wuhan local. Just as I knew that the Red Cross could be sent to Wuhan, I asked my friend to contact the Red Cross. On the first day of the New Year, these donated masks were sent to Wuhan, possibly to medical institutions and pharmacies.

Face masks are in great demand in Wuhan, because they can not be used repeatedly and need to be replaced once. N95 face masks need to be replaced in four hours in crowded places in Wuhan. Because there are droplets outside the mask, there are bacteria, in the process of removing the mask may be infected, so can not use several times. But outside of Wuhan, it can last longer.

As far as I know, there is a shortage of N95 masks on the market. The domestic one is the KN95. I didn't know much about masks, and I thought N95 was the only way to prevent infection, so I looked for N95 masks. A lot of ordinary medical masks did not buy, at that time thought that does not work.

Went to the factory at 3:00 in the morning, didn't come back with a mask

All of our goods are at night to find, during the day almost all the time in contact with people who need masks, fill out the logistics form, logistics form filling is very time-consuming. Because each express needs to be clearly classified, the mask itself into many categories, but also need to determine the number of scanning Qr Code, as well as the process of running logistics. This left me with little time during the day, so I had to finish the day, go home for a bite to eat, and then continue to search for supplies and run the factory at night.

It was hard to find the factory. It rained all the time. It never stopped. In the factory everybody is busy, the boss opens three times wages to leave the partial worker, very few people take care of you, all say to have no goods, have no goods. And at this time, more people in Hubei through friends and asked to buy a mask things. Almost everyone wants to get around 200. KN95 face masks have also gone up in price to $6, $8 and $10.

On the eve of the Lunar New Year, I was also searching for supplies and did not visit the factory until the evening. It was raining heavily that day. Scattered factories were scattered along the dark lanes of the town. Many of the factories were closed, and occasionally one or two of them shone. It's hard for me to see the name brand of the factory. I can only look for it slowly according to the organized address. That night, I brought back thousands of masks.

We went to the manufacturer at two or three o'clock in the morning, but we didn't get any masks back. All the masks were reserved. And the factory has limited raw materials, mask production can not continue.

I still have a batch of face masks to mail out, there are about three or five thousand, these face masks are found a few days ago left. Logistics, I just learned today that there is a free green channel, which is good news. A few friends in Wuhan came to me to buy a mask, the goods have not yet received, SF enquiries show goods in Wuhan but can not be delivered.

My relatives and friends in Wuhan have no problems now, but they are isolated at home and no longer go out. I remember when they first got my mask, they were so grateful, they gave me thumbs up, and now I'm, like, really positive.

Today, I continue to search for disposable masks, hoping to find KN95, I would like to send them to some villages in Hubei.
